  "explanation": "Question: Hurricanes with more feminine names are perceived as less threatening and hence lead to fewer precautionary measures by the general public. Direct tests do not show a statistically significant main effect of name femininity on fatalities (Pearson p=0.454, female-vs-male t-test p=0.358, OLS adjusted p=0.715, Negative Binomial adjusted p=0.143). There is some interaction evidence with storm category in the Negative Binomial model (p=0.001), but this is not a stable overall main effect. Interpretable models prioritize damage/intensity features (e.g., log_ndam15, pressure) over masfem, so the dataset provides weak and model-dependent support for the hypothesis."
